      "title": "了 indicating change of state",
      "explanation": "了(le) placed at the end of a sentence can indicate a change of state — something has become true that was not true before. Formula: Sentence + 了(le). For example: 她生病了(She has gotten sick — a new situation). This is different from the 了(le) that marks a completed action.",
